25:36.482 --> 25:39.305
into whom has the arm of the Lord been revealed.

25:39.345 --> 25:43.129
He grew up before him like a young plant and like a root out of dry ground.

25:43.229 --> 25:54.121
He didn't have an impressive form or majesty that we should look at him, no appearance that we should desire him.

25:54.161 --> 26:02.610
He was despised and rejected by men, a man of suffering who knew what sickness was.

26:03.522 --> 26:09.428
He was like someone people turned away from, he was despised and we didn't value him.

26:10.509 --> 26:16.715
Yet he himself bore our sicknesses and he carried our pains.

26:18.697 --> 26:32.050
But we in term regarded him stricken, struck down by God and afflicted, but he was pierced because of our rebellion, crushed because of our iniquities, punishment for our peace,

26:33.122 --> 26:36.486
was on him and we are healed by his wounds.

26:38.007 --> 26:40.029
We all want to stray like sheep.

26:41.291 --> 26:47.197
We all have turned our own way for the Lord has punished him for the iniquity of us all.

26:49.819 --> 26:55.625
This is the Jesus, this is the Jesus that we serve.

26:57.607 --> 27:00.050
You see names matter.

27:01.122 --> 27:03.046
Jesus is the king of kings.

27:03.066 --> 27:04.528
He is the Messiah.

27:04.809 --> 27:10.119
He is a manual God with us, but he is also the son of man.

27:10.179 --> 27:14.086
That's the name he chose to use.

27:15.348 --> 27:22.802
Jesus, although he was a fulfillment, a prophecy in the eternal king, he chose to be called the son of man.

27:23.714 --> 27:32.066
He identified with our humanity so that we could be bought into his divinely royal family.

27:32.106 --> 27:39.517
Like as we saw in the genealogy in Matthew, Jesus' lineage has some questionable people.

27:41.439 --> 27:49.010
But this just shows that Jesus, the Son of Man, makes room for all people in his kingdom.

27:50.914 --> 27:58.202
His family tree includes both Jews and Gentiles, both the honored and the marginalized.

28:00.164 --> 28:12.838
It just as Rahab and Ruth were included into the royal bloodline and Solomon who made so many mistakes, we too are welcome into Christ's royal family when we put our faith in him.

28:12.858 --> 28:20.306
No one is excluded or deemed unworthy prostitutes

28:20.706 --> 28:30.125
immigrants, sinners of all kinds, none are turned away by the Son of Man who gave his life for the salvation of all.

28:32.250 --> 28:38.984
And as we wrap up, I just want you to remember that you have a place and purpose in this family.

28:39.004 --> 28:42.130
You belong.

28:43.362 --> 28:52.636
Because Jesus is not just this power-hungry being that is looking mindlessly for followers, like these robots.

28:52.716 --> 28:58.344
No, he's looking to add you into this beautiful royal family.

28:58.364 --> 29:01.469
And guess what?

29:01.489 --> 29:10.162
You don't have to earn your spot because you already bought with the price that Jesus paid.

29:13.666 --> 29:16.650
Let's pray.

29:16.670 --> 29:20.536
Thank you, Jesus, just for you being you.

29:22.398 --> 29:38.420
Just for your example of humility or willingness to get down low with creation, to experience hurt and pain and suffering.

29:38.480 --> 29:42.546
And it just experienced the human condition.

29:43.010 --> 29:49.458
Thank you that you just showcased to us who you are truly.

29:52.782 --> 29:57.949
God has just asked that as we go out through the week that we just remember who you are.

29:59.210 --> 30:04.797
That you're not this far away God figure that's just unreachable.

30:05.839 --> 30:11.826
That you're not just some power hungry God in this guy just looking down

30:12.674 --> 30:25.313
wanting us to mindlessly follow you, but you are present with us, that you want to know us, that you want us included into your family.

30:28.258 --> 30:37.352
I'll just ask that you just give us grace as we go out throughout the weeks, and we just remember who you truly are.

30:39.274 --> 30:41.618
Ask all this in your name, amen.

